I think they got their money's worth. EQ is meant to be a game, not a religion. If someone wants to slam through all the content and then quit, fine by me, so long as they're generally good citizens during their stay in the game. I can't speak to how they behaved on KB, but on Vaz, IV as a whole were no worse than most, although they had some individual members who were real pieces of work (as many guilds do).<br>
<br>
It's not the path I would have chosen, which is why I never applied when Krim returned to the game the first time around before KB launched. But I find it hard to disagree with folks I respect, like Kaziqueal, when he says it's the way he wanted to play. More power to 'em. EQ is a big game, with room for lots of play styles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 891<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 9:55:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26301.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> There won't be huge amounts of trickle down gear on new server. First, the people save it in guild and to their twinks. Second, they're pushing towards higher content and skipping tons of droppable gear. And third, they have no need for plat.<br>
