<br>
At least that's what I've seen on the last couple of servers.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->You're leaving out Vazaelle, then, since out of the 4,000 or so players who joined it in its first three months of life, only a handful were over level 30 in the first three months, which one would assume even a slightly experienced player would be.<br>
<br>
When I reached LOIO about six weeks after the server had opened, there were about 20 people in the zone, in an era when it was THE place to level in your teens and 20s. Six weeks later, it was nearer to 90 people in the zone at all times. Does that really sound like experienced players to you?<br>
<br>
The facts are that there are more new players around than people on old/heavily populated servers realize, since their servers are off the front screen and are usually several screens down when new players are making their server choices. Your servers might as well not be offered to new players, in fact.<br>
<br>
If you want to see if there are new players, go to FV, KB and Vazaelle (even today) and look around the newbie zones. Lo and behold, they exist. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=castaa123>Castaa123</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.pacbell.net/jcortel/flashingcircle003.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 2361<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/03 10:01:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26301.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New blue server thoughts</span><hr size=1> Your reasoning doesn't mean there are not experienced players playing, IMO.  <br>
<br>
Experience rate is greatly reduced by crappy (read: looted by the player not player purchased) gear and lack of high level buffs.  Also take away PL-ing and you aren't going to see many about 30 in 3 months.  And if there aren't groups of lvl 50s  farming items, there are going to be zero good weapons or armor help speed players along in level.  <br>
<br>
Also new servers have a much lower population level and a lower time played per session per player.  Think this is true because mature guilds and solid in-game friendships haven't taken hold en mass.  These two factors contribute to time played.  This would account for seeing less people in 'hot' experience zones than you'd expect on an older server.<br>
<br>
